SIMPLE: microorganism
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Microorganism
<hw>Mi`cro*or"gan*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Micro-</ets> + <ets>organism</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Any microscopic form of life; a form of life too small to be seen
by the naked eye; -- particularly applied to bacteria, protozoa, yeasts,
and similar organisms, esp. such are supposed to cause infectious
diseases.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Micropantograph</ent>⟦br⟧
